{
  "texts": [
    "Weizhi et al. (2022) focused on evidence-based fake news detection, where multiple pieces of evidence are utilized to examine the truthfulness of a claim.",
    "They proposed a unified graph-based semantic structure mining framework (GET).",
    "Unlike other approaches that consider claims and evidences as sequences, they represented them as graph-structured data and utilized neighborhood propagation to capture long-distance semantic dependencies among scattered relevant snippets.",
    "GET can be primarily divided into four modules:",
    "Graph construction: In order to capture the long-distance dependency of relevant information, the authors adopted a sliding window approach to convert the original claims and evidences into graphs."
  ]
}